pros:
- Plenty of autonomy to execute your job as you envision allowing everyone to develop their technical skills;
- Teams are rewarded for great performance, and the company provides you with the opportunity to grow your team/business if you have a good plan and that means better results;
- Compensation is above average and benefits are great

cons:
- Terrible employee branding (which makes it very hard to hire great talent);
- Strategy is confusing if communicated at all. A lot of information is contained in leadership silos;
- Top-down decisions appear all the time without any context of why or even who made them (even if they contradict the strategy);
